<h3 class="big">Help: web command line interface</h3>
web CLI tools is available at <b><a href="{{.Base}}/cli">CLI</a></b>.
You may download and save it on your disk, e.g. as <em>web_cli</em>,
and use it in the following way:
<pre>
python web_cli --query="dataset=/ExpressPhysics*"
</pre>
Please use <b>--help</b> for more options.
The default output format is JSON. But you can apply filter and use plain data format, e.g.:
<pre>
python web_cli --query="dataset=/ExpressPhysics* | grep dataset.name, dataset.nevents" --format=plain
/ExpressPhysics/Run2011A-Express-v2/FEVT 13321290
...
</pre>
    
