<div style="position:absolute;left:5400px;width:900px;">
<h3 class="big">Help: web filters</h3>
web supports <b>grep</b> and <b>unique</b> filters. You can use
<b>grep</b> filter to select part of the web record. For example,
<pre>
dataset=/ZMM/Summer11-DESIGN42_V11_428_SLHC1-v1/GEN-SIM | grep dataset.nevents
</pre>
Multiple filters can be applied together, for instance
<pre>
dataset=/ZMM*/*/* | unique | grep dataset.name
</pre>
    
<div style="text-align: right">
<a href="javascript:HideTag('web_cards')">hide</a>
</div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:6300px;width:900px;">
<h3 class="big">Help: Free text based queries</h3>
If you type free text based query, e.g.
<pre>
Zee CMSSW_3
</pre>
web will match provided keywords with
appropriate web <b>key=value</b> pairs which will displayed in the input field,
in this case 
<pre>dataset=*Zee* release=CMSSW_3*</pre>
<b>Please note:</b> web queries are case-sensitive due to underlying 
restrictions from participated data-services, but in
<b>autocompletion</b> mode web will apply case-insensitive searches for
all valid datasets to find your match.

